r hall, and the Gems &amp; Minerals exhibit, which boasts one of the most extensive collections in the United States, with more than 450 rare gemstones and geodes. You can also browse exhibits on Ancient Egypt, Texas Wildlife, The Americas, African Wildlife, Chemistry, and more. You can also enter the Brown Hall of Entomology, the Planetarium and the IMAX movie theatre with additional expense.</p>\n<p>5.&nbsp;<strong>Houston Woodlands Brewery Tour (Duration: aprox. 6 hours):</strong> Sample the best of Houston&rsquo;s craft beer with a 5.5-hour brewery tour of the Woodlands&nbsp;with guided tastings at three locations. Enjoy the day worry-free, with transportation and snacks included in the tour, and meet fellow craft beer enthusiasts in a fun, relaxed environment. You will also learn the craft of beer making, find out how to distinguish between different varieties, and appreciate this familiar beverage like a true beer connoisseur. Tours will have 3 stops and may include stops at the following: Copperhead Brewery, Big Thicket Distillery, B-52 Brewery, Lone Pint Brewery, Southern Star Brewery.</p>\n<p><strong>6. City Tour and Downtown Aquarium (Duration: aprox. A day):</strong> Start your Houston vacation with a 90-minute sightseeing tour by bus that showcases the city's landmarks, historic areas and views. Hear informative commentary as your bus passes through market square and downtown locations such as Allen Parkway, Buffalo Bayou, and the midtown&nbsp;residential area. Get great photo ops of downtown Houston's skyline and museum district.&nbsp;Then you will be taken to the Houston Aquarium where you have the option to have our tour guide walk you through every gallery or wander at leisure on your own.</p>\n<p><strong>7. Sugarland Walking Food Tour (Duration: aprox. 3 hours):</strong> get an authentic taste of the food scene in the southwest Houston neighbourhood Sugar Land. Visit&nbsp;four of the best restaurants in the neighborhood, where you'll sit down for se