here success is never guaranteed. And it&rsquo;s an ode to founder Harvey Levin that takes a turn for the melodramatic in the recapping of the day TMZ broke the story of Michael Jackson&rsquo;s death. For those that haven&rsquo;t bought into the TMZ universe, the tour is still a legitimately entertaining experience, thanks to the easygoing tour guides and the atonal, irreverent videos that toe the line of decency.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Bikes and Hikes LA:</strong> for an eco-friendly, healthy way to experience Los Angeles, book a Bike and Hikes LA tour, designed for everyone from avid cyclists and hikers to beginners and the occasional biker/hiker. The 32-mile, 5-hour trek starts on legendary Route 66 in West Hollywood and take you through luxurious Beverly Hills and Bel-Air; LA&rsquo;s world-famous beach cities, Santa Monica, Venice and Marina Del Rey; and the historic movie studios of Culver City.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Warner Bros. Hollywood Studio Tour and Movie Starts&rsquo; Homes Tour (Duration: aprox. 5 hours):</strong> Feel like a movie star for the day as you explore the Warner Brothers studio and get a taste for LA celebrity culture on this 4-5 hours excursion. Get a behind-the-scene look at TV and movie sets, and learn insider information from a knowledgeable tour guide. See backlots and sound stages from Friends, Gilmore Girls, Batman, Argo and more. Visit the current one-time homes of celebrities like Halle Berry, Tom Cruise, Marilyn Monrie; and check out landmarks like the Hollywood Sign, Chateau Marmont and Rodeo Drive.</p>\n<p><strong>5. Hollywood and Beverly Hills (Duration: Aprox. 4 hours): </strong>Visit Los Angeles&rsquo; most glamorous neighborhoods and iconic sites with a 4-hour sightseeing tour in a multimedia-equipped luxury van. Watch footage that highlights Hollywood history on a 32" HDTV flat screen monitor as you cruise the palm-lined streets of Beverly Hills, and take in sweeping views of the city from Mulholland Drive. Try to spot your favorite stars as while visiting celebrity homes, and enjoy live narration from a professional guide, whose facts, trivia and insider gossip will bring your Tinseltown trip to life.</p>\n<p><strong>6. Malibu Wine Safaris:</strong> takes visitors aboard open top safari vehicles to experience the beauty of Saddlerock Ranch. The tour begins with an introduction to some of the property&rsquo;s friendly exotic animals, from bison to zebras. The safari continues into the working vineyards and ranch, where an outdoor wine tasting showcases some of the wines grown onsite. The property, originally inhabited by the Chumash, is operated by the Semler family. Safaris take place daily and last between 75 to 100 minutes.</p>\n<p><strong>7. Hollywood Food Tour (Duration: Aprox. 4 hours):</strong> Get a taste for the delicious variety of Southern Califotnia&rsquo;s food scene and its key attractions through this combination walking and driving tour with a full hour of walking at the start of the tour to view all the important Hollywood landmarks by foot and for photos opportunities. Start your food exploration inside the lobby of the Hollywood Roosevelt Hotel, home to the first Academy Awards ceremony in 1929, at 10am where you'll meet your guide. This famous intersection, which plays host to both TCL Chinese Theater and Dolby Theater (site of the annual Academy Awards ceremony) is ground zero for the city's many film ceremonies and premieres. Proceed on an exploration of a strip of interesting retail attractions along Melrose, where you'll get a chance to wander past some of the city's trend-setting boutiques and stop by the many gourmet cafes where the area celebs grab their power lunches. Head next to the famous Sunset Strip, a meeting place for rock and roll fanatics from around the world. A number of celebrated music venues, including the Viper Room and Whisky a Go Go, line its streets. Your guide, who happens to live in the area, will share amusing anecdotes about this famous thoroughfare's history and its many star-powered sightings. Finish your tour after four hours of sightseeing and noshing, your belly full from some of the city's best local eateries and a chance to view a slice of daily life in the city's famous Hollywood neighborhood.</p>\n<p><strong>8. Sunset Ranch Hollywood:</strong> for a unique tour of Griffith Park, get in the saddle with Sunset Ranch Hollywood, the only horse ranch located in greater Los Angeles. Sunset Ranch offers a variety of services and activities, including guided trail rides, boarding and lessons. A one-hour trail ride into Griffith Park includes a great view of the Hollywood Sign. A two-hour ride to the top of Griffith Park features spectacular 360-degree views of Los Angeles. A variety of other ride options are available, including Lunch Ride, Sunset Dinner Ride, BBQ Ride and Kids&rsquo; Party.</p>\n<p><strong>9. Rose Bowl Stadium Tours:</strong> The landmark Rose Bowl Stadium in Pasadena is home to the UCLA Bruins football team and the annual Rose Bowl game, aka &ldquo;The Granddaddy of Them All," held every New Year&rsquo;s Day. Rose Bowl Stadium has hosted Super Bowls, Olympic events and numerous landmark concerts. The Rose Bowl is one of two stadiums in the world to host the FIFA World Cup Finals for both men and women. The monthly Rose Bowl Flea Market features more than 2,500 vendors and welcomes 15,000 to 20,000 buyers. In 1987, Rose Bowl Stadium was added to the National Register of Historic Places and designated a National Historic Landmark. Take the <a href="http://www.discoverlosangeles.com/blog/featured-member-rose-bowl-stadium-tour">Rose Bowl Stadium Tour</a> for exclusive access to the playing field, press box, UCLA locker room and more.</p>\n<p><strong>10. Aquarium of the Pacific:</strong> arrive at the Aquarium of the Pacific in Long Beach, about 25 miles (40 km) south of central Los Angeles, head inside with your general admission ticket to begin your exploration of this marine wonderland.