u-can-eat breakfast in Orlando. Then meet the guide and the rest of the tour group on a pickup from select locations. From Orlando, it&rsquo;s approximately 1.5 hours to Crystal River, the gem of Florida's beautiful Nature Coast known as the &lsquo;home of the manatees.&rsquo; More specifically, it&rsquo;s home to one of the world's largest populations of endangered West Indian manatees. Out on the water with the provided equipment, take an optional swim or snorkel with these gentle giants alongside certified dive masters. Learn more about this harmless mammal and why it&rsquo;s under threat due to a loss of habitat. After the cruise, enjoy a picnic-style lunch overlooking the manatee sanctuary at the Crystal River National Wildlife Refuge. The adventure continues in the afternoon with a 45-minute airboat tour along the Homosassa River. Keep an eye out for manatees, dolphins and a variety of other wildlife. Finally, visit Homosassa Springs Wildlife State Park, one of the best places in the state to view manatees. Witness an entertaining and educational feeding session with a park ranger, then look for bears, panthers, alligators or even a hippo while exploring the rest of the park.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Saint Augustine Day Trip (Duration: a day):</strong> Step back in time with a visit to enchanting St Augustine &ndash; one of America&rsquo;s oldest town founded in 1565, making it the oldest European-settled town in the continental US. You will be taken around the city and see all the sights while our tour guide entertains you with by providing the town&rsquo;s history and commentary. Afterward, you&rsquo;ll have plenty of time to explore the town at your leisure, shop in the gift boutiques and dine in one of the great restaurants that line the cobblestone streets.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Kennedy Space Center and Everglades Airboat Safari (Duration: a day):</strong> experience a thrilling, 30-minute airboat tour through the grassy marsh of the St. Johns River and Lake Poinsett, at speeds up to 45 miles per hour. Visit a natural cypress swamp and look for local wildlife like alligators &mdash; the Everglades&rsquo; most formidable inhabitants &mdash; plus eagles and hundreds of species of wading birds. Then take a 20-minute ride to NASA&rsquo;s Kennedy Space Center Visitor Complex for more than six hours of exploring. Enjoy a guided tour of NASA's Launch Complex 39 rocket launch site; the Shuttle Launch Experience, which is what veteran NASA astronauts call the next best thing to an actual space shuttle launch; two IMAX films &mdash; IMAX&reg; A Beautiful Planet and Journey to Space 3D, plus a number of other shows and exhibits, including a chance to meet an astronaut at the Astronaut Encounter. There is also the breath-taking Space Shuttle Atlantis Exhibit, showcasing the historic spacecraft that tells the story of NASA&rsquo;s 30-year Space Shuttle Program. Finally, visit the LC-39 Observation Gantry and the Apollo/Saturn V Center. Listen to the thunderous sounds of a Saturn V moon rocket lift-off and watch Neil Armstrong's first steps on the moon.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>5. Explore Wild Florida from Orlando (Duration: a day):</strong> Escape to the wilderness of the Florida Everglades from Orlando on this full-day airboat adventure. Just 45-minutes south of Orlando is the Wild Florida Airboats and Wildlife Park in Kenanville, the self-proclaimed &ldquo;middle of nowhere&rdquo; destination featuring airboat tours, ranch buggy tours, a wildlife park, restaurant and more. Enjoy Florida&rsquo;s natural beauty with a 30-minute airboat ride. Hop on board a U.S. Coast Guard-certified airboat and skim the shoreline or head deep into the 4,200 acres of protected swamps, marshes and rivers of the Central Florida Everglades. Catch a glimpse of alligators, eagles, turkeys, wild boars, wading birds (known as roseate spoonbills) and other native creatures. A life jacket and ear protection are provided for each guest. Then, take a step back in time 