ation aprox. 3hrs)</p>\n<p><strong>4. Private Horse and Carriage Ride in Central Park:</strong> best to be with another friend or on a date to explore New York City&rsquo;s famous Central Park on a horse-drawn carriage. Take in the wide variety of sights and sounds and fall in love with this iconic park where over 300 well-known movies have scenes here. Also see all the famous sites, including Strawberry Fields, Cherry Hill, the Central Park Zoo, Belvedere Castle, Bethesda Fountain, Gapstow Bridge, and many more. (Duration : 15mintues up to 50minutes optional)</p>\n<p><strong>5. Brooklyn Half-Day Food &amp; Culture Tour:</strong> Brooklyn is considered one of New York City&rsquo;s coolest borough. From traditional ethnic eateries to culinary hotspots that spark national dining trends, you will be shown where to eat like a local through the Polish enclave of Greenpoint or the DUMBO in Williamsburg, whilst viewing the beautiful Prospect Park and have a big slice of Neapolitan Pizza in Park Slope for an authentic taste of Italy. Brooklyn Half-Day Food &amp; Culture Tour is the right choice for a foodie who loves to travel. (Duration : 5hours)</p>\n<p><strong>6. New York City Tour with Empire State Building Observatory and Statue of Liberty Admission:</strong> experience the Big Apple starting in the morning from Times Square, the &ldquo;beating heart&rdquo; of New York City, continue over to the ornate St. Patrick&rsquo;s Cathedral and then lunch at the authentic Little Italy. After lunch, you will be taken to the New York&rsquo;s iconic Statue of Liberty where you&rsquo;ll skip-the-line access to the statue&rsquo;s pedestal and a guided audio tour. Next, when you walk through Wall Street, where &ldquo;money never sleeps&rdquo;, you&rsquo;ll also look at the famous landmarks of Federal Hall and Trinity Church. Finish the day by heading back uptown to the Empire State Building, where you&rsquo;ll conclude the trip on a &ldquo;high note&rdquo; with skip-the-line access to this famous skyscraper&rsquo;s observatory, then come back in Times Square at the end of the day to see the different atmosphere of the NY&rsquo;s beating heart. (Duration : a day)</p>\n<p><strong>7. Bear Mountain Full-Day Cruise:</strong> Explore the gorgeous Hudson River Valley on the Circle Line cruise to Bear Mountain from New York City. Spend 2.5 hours travelling up to the Hudson River, enjoying scenic views of the Palisades, Ulysses S. Grant&rsquo;s Tomb and the beautiful rolling hills along the way. There&rsquo;s an Onboard Oktoberfest that will serve you beer and food, along with the live music on Saturdays and Sundays. Once arriving at Bear Mountain, you&rsquo;ll have three hours to spend hiking, checking out the zoo or riding the on-sire carousel before returning to New York. (Duration: Aprox. 8 hours)</p>\n<p><strong>8. Philadelphia and Amish Country Day Trip from New York:</strong> Get to know the surrounding region with this full-day tour through Philadelphia and Pennsylvania&rsquo;s Amish country. Explore one of America&rsquo;s most popular cities in Philadelphia, visiting attractions from the Liberty Bell and Independence Hall to the Benjamin Franklin Parkway, Elfreth&rsquo;s Alley and so much more. Enjoy a buggy ride through the Farm country led by an Amish driver and experience the simpler life of the Amish people. (Duration : Aprox 13 hours)</p>\n<p><strong>9. New York Beer and Brewery Tour:</strong> Sip New York&rsquo;s City&rsquo;s best pints on this beer and brewery tour through Manhattan, Brooklyn and Queens. Get an insider&rsquo;s take on the New York brewing scene as you explore with our guide, and enjoy snacks paired with cutting-edge craft beers. Try the German beers at Paulaner Brewery in Manhattan, then see what&rsquo;s on tap at the celebrated Brooklyn Brewery. Enjoy a Belgian beer at a specialty bar in Williamsburg, and finish your tour with acclaimed lagers and IPAs in the up-and-coming borough of Queens. (Duration : Aprox. 4.5 hours)</p>\n<p><strong>10. TV and Movie Locations Tour with Official NBC Studios Tour:</strong> Go behind the scenes of one of America&rsquo;s top television studios with the memorable tour that showcases the best of NBC. The interactive experience put you right in touch with the action and includes hands-on options that are perfect for visitors of all ages. Check out the sets of Saturday Night Live and the Today Show. Film your own TV segment, which you&rsquo;;; be emailed to show friends back at home. Learn about the business of producing some of the nation&rsquo;s top programming and see iconic landmarks like Radio City Music Hall as part of this incredible tour. (Duration: Aprox. 5hrs)</p>	\N	\N	\N	on	1	2017-01-12 01:22:57.882267+00	2017-01-12 01:22:57.882267+00	27	0
32	Las Vegas		\N	<h1><strong>RECOMMENDED TOURS</strong></h1>\n<h2><strong>LAS VEGAS</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>1. Grand Canyon South Rim Bus Tour (Duration: aprox. 15 hours):</strong> Explore the Grand Canyon National Park on this guided, full-day sightseeing adventure tour around the South Rim. Beginning in Las Vegas, travel to the Grand Canyon&rsquo;s South Rim and the National Geographic Visitor Center. See panoramic views from various lookout locations while learning about the history and geology of the canyon from your guide. Passing through the Mojave Desert and the Black Mountains and Grand Wash Cliffs of Arizona on the way. Arrive at the Grand Canyon National Geographic Visitor Center for lunch and souvenir shopping, then proceed to Grand Canyon National Park for several hours of exploring at the South Rim. Make scenic stops at Bright Angel Lodge, one of the original hotel destinations at the Grand Canyon South Rim and Mather Point, with the most popular overlook and trails lining the edge of the canyon. See the widest and deepest point of the Grand Canyon at over 8,400 feet deep and 21 miles across. A guided Jeep tour along the rim, complete with stunning views and an education on the canyon&rsquo;s history, geology and wildlife to maximise your time at this amazing scenic stop.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Hoover Dam Tour (Duration: aprox. 6 hours)</strong>: With a knowledgeable guide, learn about the history and mechanics of the dam through engaging and informative commentary. Walk through the displays and exhibits at the Visitor Centre. Begin your tour with descend 524 feet (160 metres) into the walls of the Black Canyon to see the Nevada Powering. Stroll through the generators and see the enormous pipe inside one of the diversion tunnels. After poking around in the depths of the earth, take the elevator back up to the Visitor Centre. Get a full picture of the Hoover Dam&rsquo;s history through the exhibits and displays that show the building of the dam and its daily operations. You can then trek over the top of the dam itself for 40 minutes, where you can pause to take photographs of Lake Mead before hopping back to the vehicle to head back to Las Vegas. On the way back, we&rsquo;ll stop for lunch and at a chocolate factory to fuel up after your day of learning, seeing and experiencing.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Madame Tussauds with Gondola Ride (Duration: flexible)</strong>: Enjoy a romantic date night during this dreamy Madame Tussauds tour on a Venetian gondola ride. At Madame Tussauds Las Vegas, take pictures with life-like wax figures of your favorite celebrities, Vegas legends and super heroes. Located on the Las Vegas Strip, step into the movies with Will Smith, pose for paparazzi with Lady Gaga, have a crazy Vegas night with Bradley Cooper or fight crime alongside Nick Fury. No trip to Venice or The Venetian would be complete without a smooth and romantic glide down the outdoor Grand Canal in an authentic Venetian gondola (if selected). Float beneath bridges as your gondolier sweeps you down the outdoor Grand Canal for a ride like no other.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Death Valley National Park (Duration: a day):</strong> Discover the lowest point in the Western Hemisphere at Death Valley National Park, the largest National Park in the US, on this guided, full-day excursion from Las Vegas. Upon arrival, visit Zabriskie Point to experience one of the park&rsquo;s most famous and spectacular views &mdash; a maze of wildly eroded and vibrantly colored badlands. Then travel the scenic loop through the multi-hued hills of Artist&rsquo;s Drive to the Badwater Basin, the lowest point in the Western Hemisphere at 282 feet below sea level. This surreal landscape features one of the largest protected salt flats in the world &mdash; too harsh for most plants and animals to survive in. Also, experience the most breathtaking view in Death Valley: Dante&rsquo;s Peak, a mountaintop overlook more than 5,000 feet above the desolation of the valley. 