cknowledge and agree that: (a) you will be solely responsible for determining the most effective, efficient and safe manner to perform each instance of Tour Guide Provider services; and (b) except for the Canarini Services, you will legally provide all necessary equipment, tools and other materials, at your own expense, necessary to perform Tour Guide Provider Services.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">You understand and agree that you have a legal obligation under the Americans with Disabilities Act and similar state laws to transport Users with Service Animals (defined by applicable state and federal law), including guide dogs for the blind and visually impaired Users, and there is no exception to this obligation for allergies or religious objections. Your knowing failure to provide services to a User with a Service Animal will constitute a material breach of this Agreement. You agree that a &ldquo;knowing failure&rdquo; to comply with this legal obligation will constitute either: (1) a cancellation of a tour booking which states the denial was due to a Service Animal along with the applicable cancellation charge; (2) a cancellation fee for cancelling the tour; and (3) cancellation of your account and usage of Canarini&rsquo;s services at Canarini&rsquo;s sole discretion.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>2.3 Your Relationship with Users.</strong> You acknowledge and agree that your provision of Tour Guide Provider Services to Users creates a direct business relationship between you and the User. Canarini is not responsible or liable for the actions or inactions of a User in relation to you, your activities, your property, or your Vehicle. You will have the sole responsibility for any obligations or liabilities to Users or third parties that arise from your provision of Tour Guide Provider Services. You acknowledge and agree that you are solely responsible for taking such precautions as may be reasonable and proper (including maintaining adequate licensees, permits, and insurance that meets the requirements of all applicable laws) regarding any acts or omissions of a User or third party. You acknowledge and agree that Company may release your contact and/or applicable information to a User upon such User&rsquo;s reasonable request. You acknowledge and agree that, unless specifically consented to by a User, you may not allow individuals other than a User and any individuals authorized by such User, during the performance of Tour Guide Provider Services for such User. You acknowledge and agree that tours will be performed without unauthorized persons, unauthorized interruption, and unauthorized stops.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>2.4 Your Relationship with Company.</strong> You acknowledge and agree that Company&rsquo;s provision to you of Canarini Services creates a direct business relationship between Company and you. Company does not, and will not be deemed to, direct or control you generally or in your performance under this Agreement specifically, including in connection with your provision of Tour Guide Provider Services, your acts or omissions, or your operation and maintenance of your Vehicle. You retain the sole right to determine when, where, and for how long you will utilize the Canarini website or the Canarini Services. You have the option, via the Canarini website, to attempt to accept or to decline or cancel or ignore a User&rsquo;s request for Tour Guide Provider Services, subject to Company&rsquo;s then-current cancellation policies. With the exception of any signage required by local law or permit/license requirements, Canarini will have no right to require you to: (a) display Canarini&rsquo;s or any of its Affiliates&rsquo; names, logos or colors; or (b) wear a uniform or any other clothing displaying Canarini&rsquo;s or any of its Affiliates&rsquo; names, logos or colors. You acknowledge and agree that you have complete discretion to provide services or otherwise engage in other business or employment activities. You clearly understand that you have the complete right to; (i) use other software application services in addition to the Canarini Services; and (ii) engage in any other occupation or business. Company retains the right to deactivate or otherwise restrict you from accessing or using the Canarini website or the Canarini Services in the event of a violation or alleged violation of this Agreement, your disparagement of Company or any of its Affiliates, your act or omission that causes harm to Company&rsquo;s or its Affiliates&rsquo; brand, reputation or business as determined by Company in its sole discretion.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>2.5 Ratings.</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>2.5.1</strong> You acknowledge and agree that: (a) after receiving Tour Guide Provider Services, a User will be prompted by Canarini to provide a rating of you and such Tour Guide Provider services and, optionally, to provide comments or feedback about you and such Tour Guide Provider services.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;"><strong>2.5.2</strong> You acknowledge that Company desires that Users have access to high-quality services via Canarini&rsquo;s website. In order to continue to receive access to the Canarini website and the Canarini Services, you must maintain an average rating by Users established by Company, as may be updated from time to time by Company in its sole discretion (&ldquo;Minimum Average Rating&rdquo;). Your average rating is intended to reflect Users&rsquo; satisfaction with your Tour Guide Provider services rather than your compliance with any of Canarini&rsquo;s policies or recommendations. In the event your average rating falls below the Minimum Average Rating, Company will notify you and may provide you, in Canarini&rsquo;s discretion, a limited period of time to raise your average rating above the Minimum Average Rating. If you do not increase your average rating above the Minimum Average 