ta associated therewith) with any third party. The foregoing license grant will immediately terminate and you will not use the Canarini website in the event that you cease to provide Tour Guide Provider services using Your Device. You agree that: (i) use of the Canarini website on Your Device requires an active data plan with a wireless carrier associated with Your Device, which data plan will be provided by you at your own expense; and (ii) use of the Canarini Services on Your Device as an interface with the Canarini Services may consume very large amounts of data through the data plan. CANARINI RECOMMENDS THAT YOUR DEVICE ONLY BE USED UNDER A DATA PLAN WITH UNLIMITED OR VERY HIGH DATA USAGE LIMITS, AND CANARINI WILL NOT BE RESPONSIBLE OR LIABLE FOR ANY FEES, COSTS, OR OVERAGE CHARGES ASSOCIATED WITH ANY DATA PLAN.</p>\n<h4>3. TOUR GUIDE SERVICE PROVIDER REQUIREMENTS</h4>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>3.1 Your Requirements.</strong> You acknowledge and agree that at all times, you will: (a) hold and maintain all licenses, permits, approvals and authority applicable to you that are necessary to provide Tour Guide Provider services to third parties in the Territory; (b) possess the appropriate and current level of training, expertise and experience to provide Tour Guide Provider Services in a professional manner with due skill, care and diligence; (c) perform the tour guide provider services for all booking requests that you accept; (d) familiarize yourself with all applicable local, state, and federal laws related to Canarini Services and your Tour Guide Service Provider services, (d) maintain high standards of professionalism, service and courtesy; (e) immediately contact Canarini should issues arise, (e) complete tour guide training as required by Canarini, (f) update your Tour Guide information and calendar frequently to reflect your current contact information and availability, (g) cease using Canarini services and immediately inform Canarini if anything occurs which impairs your ability to abide by this Agreement and lawfully perform tour guide(s) (e.g. criminal activity, unsound mind, etc.), (g) agree to our payment service provider&rsquo;s terms, (h) receive text messages (in which you will be solely responsible for text/data charges) at the number you provide us and to always update the number provided to us to reflect your current telephone number, and (i) comply with Canarini&rsquo;s Diversity Inclusion Policy.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong><u>DIVERSITY Inclusion Policy</u></strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Canarini holds the principles of inclusion and respect with great importance and has developed the Canarini Inclusion Policy to underscore its commitment to these important principles. Canarini&rsquo;s inclusive environment requires mutual respect and diversity inclusion by Tour Guide Providers. In an inclusive environment, our users should feel safe&nbsp;from abuse, harassment, and unfair criticism.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Bias, prejudice, racism, and hatred are strictly disallowed. Tour Guide Providers are required to follow all applicable laws that prohibit discrimination based on factors such as race, religion, sexual orientation, national origin, and others.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Tour Guide Providers are required to be respectful of users and others in interactions and encounters while providing their services. It is our hope that users&rsquo; diversity of background experiences, beliefs, and customs will enrich the lives of Tour Guide Service Providers as well. By connecting people from different backgrounds, Canarini hopes to build better understanding and as a result a better experience for all.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>3.2 Background</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">You acknowledge and agree that you may be subject to certain background and driving record checks from time to time in order to qualify to provide, and