213	Chicago Crime and Mob Tour (Duration: approx. 90 minutes)		\N	<p>Your tour will begin in Chicago&rsquo;s Near North Side, across the street from Water Tower Place, where you will board your coach vehicle.&nbsp; On board, an experienced guide narrates during your 1.5-hour tour of Chicago&rsquo;s famed criminal and historical sights. Listen to thrilling stories of mobsters, violence and crime as your coach winds through Chicago&rsquo;s historic River North, Gold Cost, Lincoln Park, Old Town, Loop and Magnificent Mile. Snap pictures and enjoy little-known tales of legendary mobsters Al Capone, &lsquo;Terrible&rsquo; Tommy O&rsquo;Conner, and Bugs Moran. &nbsp; Your mafia tour highlights Chicago&rsquo;s most notorious crime scenes, including the courthouse where some of the most famed mob cases were tried, and the site of the grisly 1929 St. Valentine&rsquo;s Day Massacre. Other notorious mob haunts you do a drive-by on are the Biograph Theater, Holy Name Cathedral, Clark Street Bridge, and Lake Street EL.</p>	chicago.jpg	\N	\N	on	1	2017-03-17 03:52:22.404779+00	2017-03-17 03:52:22.404779+00	60	4
214	Famous Tastes of Chicago (Duration: approx. 3 hours)		\N	<p>Discover Chicago&rsquo;s food, history, architecture and culture on this 3-hour, small-group walking tour. Your walking adventure will visit (subject to change):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pizano&rsquo;s Pizza has been a family tradition, serving &ldquo;World famous gourmet deep dish pizza&rdquo;, for over 60 years. The best in Chicago!</li>\n<li>The Goddess and the Baker&mdash; Enjoy a chocolate dessert from this local bakery and cafe. Specializing in desserts all day, this unique spot also offers gourmet coffee, breakfast, lunch and dinner.</li>\n<li>The Berghoff is oldest family run-establishment in Chicago. Opening in 1898, it now serves Chicagoans, &lsquo;tradition with a twist&rsquo;, as well as classic German favorites and their own line of beers.&nbsp;Special Note: From November 22 until January 1, the Berghoff will be replaced with the Billy Goat Tavern.</li>\n<li>Sugar Bliss Cake Boutique, a cupcake shop and more unique to Chicago! Any of their confections is sure to satisfy just about any sweet tooth.</li>\n<li>Taste a classic Italian beef sandwich at Al&rsquo;s Beef, who&rsquo;ve been making these famous Chicago sandwiches since 1938.</li>\n<li>Fannie May Chocolates has been serving Chicagoans decadent chocolates since 1920.</li>\n<li>Visit the Chicago Cultural Center, home to the world&rsquo;s largest Tiffany glass ceiling. (Note: Chicago Cultural Center is closed most holidays). Learn about landmarks like the Art Institute of Chicago, City Hall, Willis Tower, Daley Plaza and more! Get a glimpse of Chicago&rsquo;s famous Millennium Park and &ldquo;The Bean&rdquo; as we walk by.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Along the way, see and learn about the historical, cultural and architectural components that make up this legendary town.</p>	chicago.jpg	\N	\N	on	1	2017-03-17 03:55:14.96308+00	2017-03-17 03:55:14.96308+00	60	5
215	Chicago Prohibition Tour (Duration: approx. 3 hours and 30 minutes)		\N	<p>Start your 3.5-hour Chicago Prohibition tour at the Green Door Tavern &mdash; a vintage downtown bar built in 1872 and decorated with antiques and Americana collectibles that give it a sense of old-time Chicago. Be sure to bring along your government-issued ID and some cash to purchase craft cocktails and signature drinks made by expert bartenders on this adults-only tour. Your entertaining guide illuminates the underground world of Chicago&rsquo;s historic speakeasies used during Prohibition and still in operation today. Learn why the sale of alcohol was banned in the US from 1920 to 1933, and discover Prohibition&rsquo;s key players. Hear anecdotes about lawbreakers like Al Capone and other Chicago mobsters who became powerful during the dry years. Pull up a stool at a cocktail lounge in Wicker Park where great blues music pumps from an old jukebox. You'll also enjoy a neighbourhood bar that claims to be the oldest and longest-running tavern in the Old Town district.</p>	chicago.jpg	\N	\N	on	1	2017-03-17 03:55:55.073302+00	2017-03-17 03:55:55.073302+00	60	6
216	The twenties Art Deco and Decadence Tour (Duration: approx. 3 hours)		\N	<p>Discover&nbsp;the lifestyles from the 1920s and 1930s alongside Chicago&rsquo;s Art Deco architecture. Begin by exploring the history of speakeasies with a tour of a former Chicago establishment. Talk with the professional guide about the effects Prohibition had on Chicago, including the rise of the Chicago Outfit, a powerful, influential, and dangerous Italian-American organized crime syndicate. Learn about the history of Art Deco architecture and see examples of it throughout Chicago. Using old pictures, brief videos, and music, discover more about this exciting era of Chicago history. At every Art Deco building stop, find at least one exciting topic that defined the era &mdash; like the World&rsquo;s Fair in 1933 to 1934, Prohibition, Chicago flappers and Civil Rights activist Josephine Baker, plus notorious American gangster Al Capone, and more.</p>	chicago.jpg	\N	\N	on	1	2017-03-17 03:56:38.471077+00	2017-03-17 03:56:38.471077+00	60	7
