247	Spa & Wellness		\N	<p><strong>Skoah Newbury (641A Tremont St, Boston, MA 02118)</strong>: this is the spa for those who are looking for a little pampering but not all the fuss and fluff that goes along with a day at a traditional spa. A gym for your skin, Skoah's focus is on the face. Offering memberships for those who are serious about skin care or single visit options for those who are passing through town, Skoah helps you incorporate a spa service into your busy schedule. With options that get you in out and glowing in about an hour so you can keep on schedule to more in depth pampering Skoah has a treatment for you. Enjoy a little extra by opting for the soothing, customized, deluxe 'facialiscous' facial that includes a mini massage along with your cleansing or get as little as a 'quickie' which has you off the table in 20 minutes. With an extensive product line, you may just find your skin care regimen at Skoah.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Corbu (5 Bennett St, Cambridge, MA 02138)</span></strong>: Taking 'farm to table' to the next level is Corbu, the Charles Hotel Spa in Harvard Square that brings seasonal and local to your skin. Inspired by chefs of the hotel's famed restaurants, Corbu's Spa Director shops area farmer's markets and makes many of the salt scrubs, sugar scrubs and lotions. In addition to their fabulous "farm to table" treatments, Corbu is the first New England spa to use mySkin. Based on principles of science and sophisticated algorithms mySkin is used to analyze your skin type in order to find you the perfect set of products to care for your unique needs.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Equinox Fitness Club, Health Spa Fitness (4 Avery Street, Boston, MA 02111)</span></strong>: Equinox is more than a spa, it a high end, full service gym. Bostonians in the know join Equinox for top notch fitness, but take advantage of the on-site spa after workouts. Although it is not easy for non-members to enjoy the gym (having to shell out $50 for a day pass) a service at the spa at Equinox allows you instant access. Book a massage, facial, wax, body treatment tan or healing session and enjoy the gym and its amenities for the day. If you have children with you, take advantage of the on-site daycare while you get in a good workout and enjoy your spa service. Then get glamorous in their state of the art locker room stocked with Kheils products before heading back out onto the bustling Boston streets.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Inman Oasis (243 Hampshire Street, Cambridge, MA 02139)</span></strong>: Here you'll get all relaxation you want, with a strong focus on water. Inman Oasis provides guests with a nice soak in one of their hot tubs followed by a massage. The focus is on healing and relaxing the body itself. Inman Oasis only offers massage therapy and hot tub soaks, leaving you with a targeted treatment. The hot soak prior to your massage can help maximize the effect of even the shortest massage. The vibe at Inman Oasis is laid back and welcoming allowing even the spa phobic the chance to give it a shot and feel comfortable.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Bliss Spa (W Boston, 100 Stuart Street, Boston, MA 02116)</span></strong>: Bliss spa is like no other- upbeat in nature, it invites a more social spa experience. Lively music pumps throughout, headphones are available to enjoy a show on their televisions, or listen to your choice of tunes. The ultra-modern surroundings are filled with bright pops of color and the small bites provided are not your typical spa cuisine (brownies anyone). Treatments are done with Bliss products that can be purchased for you at home enjoyment. Food and drinks can be ordered and enjoyed while you're undergoing your Bliss experience from Market Restaurant on the first floor of the W Hotel that is home to Bliss.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Pyara Spa and Salon (1050 Massachusetts Avenue, Cambridge, MA 02138)</span></strong>: is an Aveda product specialist using their 97% naturally derived ingredient products for your services. Upstairs, you'll find a well-appointed, modern chic salon and retail space, while downstairs you'll escape reality in their calm and inviting spa. Rooms are set-up to create the ideal setting for your services. Built in Vichy showers, with adjoining shower stall for rinsing without the need to leave your room for the locker room mid service, and couples units are just a couple of the reminders that Pyara has put a lot of attention into the detail of their spa. Services can be customized, by the specialists on staff to ensure that each guest gets exactly what they need. arrive a few moments prior to your service starting to savor a cup of tea in the spa waiting area then get ready to be well cared for.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Bella Sante Day Spa (38 Newbury Street, MA 02116)</span></strong>: The Newbury Street location is a stunning space with tall ceilings, architectural detail and an elegant lounge that features expansive windows overlooking Newbury Street and letting in lots of light. A focus on relaxation for their upscale clientele means that you'll feel like a million bucks before your treatments even begin. Offering nine spa treatment rooms, his and her locker rooms, three pedi seats and four mani tables you'll find what you need at Bella Sante. Enjoy their amenities which include a steam room, before or after your appointment and face the rest of your day refreshed.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Exhale (Advisors Living, 28 Arlington St or Batter Wharf Hotel, 2 Battery Wharf, MA 02109)</span></strong>: Exhale Spa lets you come in to relax and treat your mind, body and soul to something special. At Exhale Spa, you will find yourself whisked of the city streets and into a space that invites you to let go. Starting with the boutique stocked with the big names in chic exercise attire and accessories you may want to buy your outfit before participating in one of their classes. Exhale is not just a place to pamper your outside, it is also ideal for those looking to partake in a little exercise. Offering Core Fusion and Yoga classes, indulge your need for staying fit before enjoying the steam shower, or sauna. If you're at the Battery Wharf Hotel location make time for the Hamman where the heat and steam helps any special moisturizers soak in. Loosen your muscles with a relaxing massage or treat your skin to something special like a facial, scrub or wrap. Those who seek a more holistic treatment will be pleased with Exhale's selection including acupuncture, reiki and cupping.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">G2O Spa &amp; Salon (278 Newbury Street, Boston, MA 02116)</span></strong>: a full-service spa and salon that will make your spa day dreams come true. Here, you'll be escorted to the relaxation area where you can slip out of your street clothes and into a cozy robe. Arrive early as the amenities are amazing and any service entitles you to enjoy all that G2O has to offer. Take a dip in their hot tub, chill with friends in the fireside lounge or on the patio when the weather is warm, take a deep breath and relax in the brine relaxation room and even bring in your own bottle of bubbly and even some snacks because G2O has a kitchenette at your disposal. With a wide range of services that include acupuncture, a nap pod and an experience room where steam, light, sound, scents and water converge, you can truly spend an entire day at this spa.</p>\n<p><strong><span class="bold">Mandarin Spa (Mandarin Oriental Hotel, 776 Boylston Street, Boston, MA 02199)</span></strong>: Enter a world where relaxation is all you'll know. Feel every worry vanish as you indulge the needs of your inner and outer self at the Mandarin Spa. A truly Zen retreat, Mandarin Spa is perched within the Mandarin Oriental. Enjoy a single spa treatment, a full day, a couples retreat or a few customized selections from their menu of services and you'll be treated to a day of pure relaxation. Starting the moment, you approach the desk when you are whisked out of your street shoes and into their slippers, you'll begin your journey from stressed to calm, cool and collected. Enjoy time in the heat and water facilities before making your way to the relaxation beds where you'll be met by your therapist and led through the facility to your treatment room. Here, you'll complete your visit and receive personalized care under the expert hands of the spa staff.</p>	MASS MoCA.jpg	\N	\N	on	1	2017-04-20 02:40:07.29311+00	2017-04-20 02:40:07.29311+00	33	5
248	Spa & Wellness		\N	<p><strong>Espa at Acqualina Resort &amp; Spa (17875 Collins Avenue, Sunny Isles Beach, 33160)</strong>: ESPA has already built a reputation for quality in Europe, and it is no surprise to see this spa uphold its high standards in the United States.The spa is located in the stunning Acqualina Resort &amp; Spa, perfectly positioned near Bal Harbour shopping district. With a style that focuses on complete relaxation, offering holistic, meditative and restorative treatments based on Ayuryedic principles, the spa is a world-class addition to the ESPA family. Signature treatments include:&nbsp;The 80-minute Anti-Ageing Active Peel Facial, the Stress Releasing Abyhanga, and the ESPA Time.</p>\n<p><strong>The Spa at Mandarin Oriental (500 Brickell Key Drive, Miami 33131)</strong>: Having recently undergone a four-month refurbishment, the Spa is one of the finest health clubs in Miami. Located in the Mandarin Oriental, the Spa has created an experience that blends elements from a variety of backgrounds, from Chinese through Ayurvedic, European, and Baliness to Thai. With 17 treatment rooms, stunning floorto-ceiling views and a fully equipped fitness centre, the Spa presents guests with a host of different options for relacation and rejuvenation. Signature treatments include: Mandarin Oriental Spa Therapies, Kundalini Journey, Oriental Essence, and Sun Ritual. The Spa also offers its guests a highly personalized experience, which focuses on the individual&rsquo;s needs.</p>\n<p><strong>Pritikin Longevity Center &amp; Spa (8755 NW 36th Street, Miami 33178)</strong>: has long been a well-established destination for those looking to improve their health, lose weights, or just relax. Physicians, dieticians, physiologists and psychologists are on hand with advice on everything from stress, heart fitness, sexuality and instructions on how to eat more healthily. It&rsquo;s a fantastic venue for those looking to improve their lifestyle or simply unwind for a day. Situated just to the west of the city with signature treatments include: signature body polish, an exfoliation using Dead Sea mineral salts and a body mask.</p>\n<p><strong>The Carillon Hotel and Spa - formerly known as Canyon Ranch Hotel &amp; Spa Miami Beach (6801 Collins Avenue, Miami Beach, 33141)</strong>: not only the place is situated on a beautiful stretch of 750 feet of unspoiled white beach, but it is also within easy reach of the South Beach scene. There are plenty of opportunities to relax with a 70,000 square-foot wellness spa, 150 luxurious suites and four dining venues. On hand are physicians and other health professionals to provide medical advice for those looking to address any health concern, or just simply want to indulge in relaxation. Signature treatments include: Muscle Melt for Road Warriors, a traditional Thai massage using lemongrass oil and warm herbal pouches pressed into muscles.</p>\n<p><strong>Spa V at Hotel Victor (1144 Ocean Drive, Miami Beach, 33139)</strong>: just steps from the bustling South Beach scene, Spa V is an underground sanctuary that is fit for a modern-day sultan. Scattered pillows, daybeds and subdued lighting complement a co-ed steam bath, cool-down room and South Beach&rsquo;s first traditional Turkish Hamman. With European influences aplenty, and an ambiance that is stylish and sultry, visitors are likely to find the Spa V a calming refuge of sumptuousness and tranquility. Fans of Sa V include former Miami Heat basketball player Shaquile O&rsquo;Neal. Signature treatments include: the Victor of invigorating body scrub utilizing essential oils, a destressing Stone Me massage with hot stones and oil, and a Visage pour Homme facial.</p>\n<p><strong>The Spa at the Miami Beach EDITION (2910 Collins Avenue, Miami Beach, FL 33140)</strong>: a luxurious, 1800 square-foot spa offering a state-of-the-art fitness studio, an epically stocked retail shop, a beauty lounge, and a draped, candlelit relaxation room. Featuring nine private treatment rooms including a detox room with a steam shower, a Beauty Lounge for nail, hair and makeup services, spacious locker rooms with a steam room, The Spa at The Miami Beach EDITION offers guests a wide range of services in a soothing, relaxing environment. The spa&rsquo;s massage, skincare, detox, scrub, and couple&rsquo;s rooms are all equipped with their own iPads, so you can handpick your own music to drift off to. Signature treatments include: sticks and stones massage is in interplay of bamboo sticks rolling across the body with warm stones encouraging the body to release fascial adhesions and relax the muscles.</p>\n<p><strong>Trump National Doral Miami (4400 NW 87th Avenue, Doral, FL 33178)</strong>: Home to the Miss Universe contestants while they prepped for the pageant, the Trump National Doral spa boasts 33 treatment rooms and over 100 services for girls, guys and couples. Day packages start at $175, which gives you a facial and massage, access to Trump&rsquo;s fitness center, pools, hydrotherapies, and lunch or dinner at one of the resort&rsquo;s restaurants.</p>\n<p><strong>Lapis Spa (4441 Collins Avenue, Miami Beach, FL 33140)</strong>: Martha Stewart stamps this as &ldquo;the most beautiful spa in America&rdquo;, so if you&rsquo;re going to book a treatment at Lapis Spa, then you might as well go big and reserve the Bleau private spa suite. There are two treatment beds, a jetted tub and a private bathroom and shower that accompany your oceanside view. Once you&rsquo;re done with your Aroma Detox therapy, you can bequest a personal bath butler to cater to your bubbling needs.</p>\n<p><strong>The Wellness Garden and Spa at The Besty (1440 Ocean Drive, Miami Beach, FL 33139)</strong>: As the only full-service, rooftop bar in all of Miami, the Wellness Garden and Spa at The Besty Hotel is a slice of serenity on Ocean Drive. It&rsquo;s one of the only places you can find a facial make of 99 percent pure nano gold, which makes the spa&rsquo;s &ldquo;Moment of Gold&rdquo; facial a definite anti-aging treatment. One thing that makes The Besty unique, is that every treatment begins with a foot washing and ends with you bringing home an aromatherapy pouch. But the best part about the Betsy, even better than the fact that you can get your services poolside in a cabana, is that you can get everything done at night under the stars. Signature treatment includes: Moment of Gold.</p>\n<p><strong>The Spa at Viceroy Miami (485 Brickell Avenue, Miami, FL 33131)</strong>: boasts a 5,000-square-foot water lounge with a floating library, hot and cold plunge pools and a breath-taking view of the bay. Besides the gorgeous Philippe Starck designed interior, the Viceroy has world-class treatments you can enjoy in one of its ten spa treatment rooms, like its collagen-filled Dr. Babor facial or its medical-grade HydraFacial MD treatment. If you are itching for something full-body, they have everything from sports massages to a Jet Lag Cure.</p>	Miami Beach.jpg	\N	\N	on	1	2017-04-20 02:51:48.148182+00	2017-04-20 02:51:48.148182+00	34	5
